China and Vietnam "Peaceful Rescue-2021" security joint exercise successfully concluded - Xinhua Xinhua News Agency, Hanoi, Dec. 12 (Zhou Na Teng Huaijin) 12 morning, the Chinese participants in the "Peaceful Rescue-2021" security joint exercise between the two armies The detachment all safely returned to the territory of Guangxi, China, marking the successful completion of the training mission, which lasted 7 days. The joint exercise, the two armies around the humanitarian medical rescue of this major subject, closely related to the mission of the guard to save lives and help the wounded, in accordance with operational standards to complete the joint guard command, joint field rescue, bulk casualty disposal and other course content, effectively enhance the two armies guard security capabilities. The results of the exercise were affirmed by the Chinese and Vietnamese armies. Nguyen Hung Thanh, director of the Vietnamese exercise steering committee and deputy director and chief of staff of the General Department of Logistics of the Vietnam People's Army, said at the end ceremony of the exercise that through the exercise, Vietnamese military doctors learned from Chinese military doctors about the organization of the exercise and professional activities, and also saw the medical and security equipment of the Chinese side. The results achieved in the exercise proved the professional capabilities of the military medical forces of the two countries in medical assistance, epidemic prevention and control. Chen Chunming, head of the Chinese Steering and Coordination Group and deputy director of the Health Bureau of the Central Military Commission's Logistics Security Department, said the exercise is another pioneering and innovative practice based on the successful holding of a joint medical clinic in 2018, which is a very important milestone. During the exercise, the Chinese People's Liberation Army donated medical protective masks, medical protective clothing, rapid nucleic acid testing instruments and other health and epidemic prevention materials to the Vietnam People's Army.
